      <h1><a href="https://charts.helm.sh/">charts</a></h1>
      

      <h1 id="helm-stable">Helm Stable</h1>

<p><a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache%202.0-blue.svg" alt="License" /></a></p>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p><a href="https://helm.sh">Helm</a> must be installed to use the charts.
Please refer to Helm’s <a href="https://helm.sh/docs/">documentation</a> to get started.</p>

<p>Once Helm is set up properly, add the repo as follows:</p>

<div class="language-console highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="go">helm repo add stable https://charts.helm.sh/stable
</span></code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can then run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">helm search repo stable</code> to see the charts, or browse on CNCF <a href="https://artifacthub.io/packages/search?page=1&amp;repo=helm-stable">Artifact Hub</a>.</p>

<h2 id="contributing">Contributing</h2>

<!-- Keep full URL links to repo files because this README syncs from master to gh-pages.  -->
<p>⚠️ Note the <a href="https://github.com/helm/charts/blob/master/README.md#status-of-the-project">status of the project</a>, <a href="https://github.com/helm/charts/blob/master/README.md#deprecation-timeline">deprecation timeline</a>, and the ongoing effort to <a href="https://github.com/helm/charts/issues/21103">relocate charts to new repos</a>.</p>

<!-- Keep full URL links to repo files because this README syncs from master to gh-pages.  -->
<p>We’d love to have you contribute! Please refer to our <a href="https://github.com/helm/charts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md">contribution guidelines</a> for details.</p>

